<p>Where does the city's money come from? Three sources do most of the work: property tax (30%), sales tax (21%), and interfund transfers (16%). After that, overhead (9%) and the utility user tax (6%) round out the top five, with the remaining 18% spread across grants, reimbursements, services, franchise fees, and smaller categories. On the spending side, salaries and benefits dominate — 45% in 26–27 and rising to 51% the following year as one-time construction spending falls off. Services and supplies come next at 35–38%, followed by interfund transfers at 11–12%.</p>

