<h2>What's Next</h2>

<p>Tuesday's session was a workshop, not a vote. The Council was asked for direction on priorities and funding approach — which discretionary items to incorporate into the draft budget, which to defer, and which to drop. The Council's next regular meeting is scheduled for <strong>Tuesday, May 13, 2026</strong>, and the full FY 26–27 / 27–28 budget will return for adoption in the weeks that follow. Workshop materials, including the full presentation deck and individual funding requests, are posted on the city's agenda center at <em>cloverdale.net/agendacenter</em>.<span class="endmark"></span></p>

